meta-custom overview
====================

`meta-custom` bundles the DES in-vehicle software layers that sit on top of
Poky/meta-qt6.  The layers are organised by responsibility so each hardware or
UX feature can evolve independently:

* **meta-app** – Packages the Qt-based HeadUnit and Instrument Cluster user
  interfaces and their systemd service units.  Source trees are consumed from
  sibling workspaces so UI developers can iterate outside of Yocto.
* **meta-env** – Captures platform policy: base image recipe, boot overlays,
  distro configuration, and core services such as D-Bus or networking tweaks.
* **meta-piracer** – Provides PiRacer-specific enablement, including SocketCAN
  helpers, the gamepad controller daemon, and the Python hardware abstraction
  modules the controller depends on.

Adding the layers
-----------------

Enable the layers in your build environment:

.. code-block:: bash

   bitbake-layers add-layer meta-custom/meta-app
   bitbake-layers add-layer meta-custom/meta-env
   bitbake-layers add-layer meta-custom/meta-piracer

Once added, the reference image recipe
``meta-custom/meta-env/recipes-core/images/des-image.bb`` pulls in the head unit
UI, instrument cluster, and controller components by default.

External source expectations
----------------------------

Several recipes (for example the HeadUnit and Instrument Cluster applications)
stage their sources from sibling directories such as ``Head-Unit`` or
``DES_Instrument-Cluster``.  Ensure those checkouts are present relative to the
Yocto build directory, or override the corresponding ``*_SRC`` variables in
``local.conf``/``.bbappend`` files.
